<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Pipeline on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/pipeline/</link><description>Recent content in Pipeline on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/pipeline/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash Pipe Failure Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/pipe-failure/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/pipe-failure/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-pipe-failure-error-fix"&gt;Bash Pipe Failure Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a command in a pipeline fails and the failure isn&amp;rsquo;t properly detected or handled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By default, Bash only returns the exit status of the &lt;strong&gt;last&lt;/strong&gt; command in a pipeline. If an earlier command fails but the last succeeds, the pipeline reports success. The &lt;code&gt;set -o pipefail&lt;/code&gt; option changes this so the pipeline returns the status of the last failing command.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Jenkins Pipeline Syntax Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/jenkins/pipeline-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/jenkins/pipeline-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="jenkins-pipeline-syntax-error"&gt;Jenkins Pipeline Syntax Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A pipeline syntax error means the Jenkinsfile contains invalid Groovy syntax or uses incorrect Jenkins pipeline DSL. Jenkins cannot parse the pipeline definition and fails before execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing or mismatched braces, brackets, or quotes in the Jenkinsfile&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using declarative syntax inside scripted pipeline blocks (or vice versa)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Referencing an undefined variable or function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect use of pipeline steps (e.g., &lt;code&gt;sh&lt;/code&gt; with wrong argument type)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="validate-jenkinsfile-syntax"&gt;Validate Jenkinsfile Syntax&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Use the Jenkins Pipeline Linter&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;java -jar jenkins-cli.jar declarative-linter &amp;lt; Jenkinsfile
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-common-declarative-pipeline-structure"&gt;Check Common Declarative Pipeline Structure&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pipeline &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; agent any
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; stages &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; stage&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Build&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; steps &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sh &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;make build&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-quoting-issues"&gt;Fix Quoting Issues&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: mixed quotes
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sh echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Building version $VERSION&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sh &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;echo Building version ${env.VERSION}&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-block-nesting"&gt;Fix Block Nesting&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: missing closing braces
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;pipeline &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; stages &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; stage&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Build&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; steps &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sh &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;make&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// missing }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-pipeline-syntax-generator"&gt;Use Pipeline Syntax Generator&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jenkins &amp;gt; Pipeline Syntax (under Tools section)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-groovy" data-lang="groovy"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Undefined variable
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;echo $&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;UNDEFINED_VAR&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ERROR: No such property: UNDEFINED_VAR
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fix: define the variable or use env.UNDEFINED_VAR
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Wrong step argument type
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sh&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;([&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;cmd1&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;cmd2&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;])&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ERROR: expects String, got List
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fix: sh command: &amp;#39;cmd1 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; cmd2&amp;#39;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/jenkins/build-failed/"&gt;Build Failed&lt;/a&gt; — build step returned error&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/jenkins/scm-error/"&gt;SCM Error&lt;/a&gt; — source checkout failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PowerShell PipelineStoppedException Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/pipeline-failed/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/powershell/pipeline-failed/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="powershell-pipelinestoppedexception-fix"&gt;PowerShell PipelineStoppedException Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a running pipeline is stopped before all commands have completed. The error message reads: &lt;code&gt;PipelineStoppedException: The pipeline has been stopped.&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PowerShell pipelines stream data between commands. If an upstream command fails, is interrupted by the user, or throws a terminating error, the entire pipeline is stopped. Downstream commands receive this exception when they attempt to read from the pipeline after it has been halted.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Build Step Marked Build as Failure</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/jenkins/build-failed/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/jenkins/build-failed/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;This error means a step in the Jenkins pipeline or freestyle build returned a failure status. Jenkins marks the overall build as failed and may trigger failure notifications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A shell script or command in the build step exited with a non-zero code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A test suite reported failures and the step is configured to fail on test failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A post-build action (like artifact archiving) could not complete&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Environment variables or credentials are missing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How To Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check the console output for the specific step and failing command. Use &lt;code&gt;try/catch&lt;/code&gt; in scripted pipelines to handle expected failures:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>